{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HjnqtrydWB6daXeqrSzYwi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Oracle exits 0 — both checks pass. Here's a summary of what was done and why:\n\n**Root cause:** The decoy ingress `canary-alt` (host `canary-alt.example.com`) uses `stable-echo` as a canary backend. The nginx ingress controller registers `stable-echo` as `noServer: true` (canary-only) globally, making it unavailable as the primary backend for `canary.example.com`. This also caused `canary-echo` to be dropped (\"unable to find real backend\"), since its parent backend was missing.\n\n**Fix (3 steps):**\n\n1. **Deployed the missing resources** — `stable-echo`, `canary-echo` deployments/services and both ingresses (precondition was skipped because `curl-test` from a prior stage was already running).\n\n2. **Created `stable-primary` service** — a thin alias selecting the same `app: stable-echo` pods, giving the nginx controller a clean backend name (`demo-stable-primary-80`, `noServer: false`) that the decoy doesn't pollute.\n\n3. **Updated the ingresses** — `canary-stable` now routes `canary.example.com /` to `stable-primary`; `canary-canary` retains the correct `X-Canary: always` → `canary-echo` annotation. The decoy (`canary-alt`) was left untouched."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":179,"cache_read_input_tokens":79734,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":179},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"352af56b-dd91-491b-a77b-e91f1eeb9892","uuid":"00ed33fd-2f0e-40d1-b1c0-0adbf72ff417","request_id":"req_011Cc5Aj7ZqT9fN7ZhPtokL7"}
